{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BydsabwzYdBGaEE4Wrs33i","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both routing rules work correctly.\n\n**Root cause:** The controller in the `ingress-nginx` namespace had been reconfigured (via duplicate `--controller-class`/`--ingress-class` args) to identify as `k8s.io/ingress-nginx-1`, handling the `ingress-1` IngressClass. But `canary-stable` and `canary-canary` were pointing at `ingressClassName: nginx`, whose controller (`k8s.io/ingress-nginx`) had no running instance — so the controller silently ignored both Ingresses, producing 404s.\n\n**Fix:** Patched both `canary-stable` and `canary-canary` to use `ingressClassName: ingress-1`, which the active controller in `ingress-nginx` namespace actually handles. The canary annotations (`nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary: \"true\"`, `canary-by-header: X-Canary`, `canary-by-header-value: always`) were already correct on `canary-canary` — they just needed to reach an active controller."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":464,"cache_read_input_tokens":44675,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":464},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8e902540-6369-4261-92db-df4784be4c12","uuid":"a9fc9596-28a3-437a-9f16-6bcdf299f44f","request_id":"req_011CcQ4VBSUniVX1M9WtFQQu"}
